ZH: 空口无凭，你说的话没有证据。
EN: Without evidence, your words are baseless.

ZH: 他只是空口无凭地指责了她。
EN: He accused her without any evidence.

ZH: 她说的话都是空口无凭的。
EN: What she said was all baseless talk.

ZH: 不要空口无凭地传播谣言。
EN: Don't spread rumors without evidence.

ZH: 他们只是空口无凭地谴责了他。
EN: They condemned him without any evidence.

ZH: 空口无凭的言论很容易引起误会。
EN: Baseless remarks can easily lead to misunderstandings.

ZH: 警方表示，目前还没有证据，所以空口无凭。
EN: The police stated that there is no evidence at present, so it's baseless.

ZH: 所有的指控都是空口无凭的。
EN: All accusations are baseless.

ZH: 这种空口无凭的指责很不负责任。
EN: This kind of baseless accusation is very irresponsible.

ZH: 别随随便便就对别人的动机进行空口无凭的猜测。
EN: Don't make baseless guesses about others' motives casually.

ZH: 他没有证据，只是在空口无凭地猜测。
EN: He has no evidence, just baseless guesses.

ZH: 这些言词空空如也，毫无凭据可言。
EN: These words are empty and baseless.

ZH: 他的反驳毫无根据，充满了空口无凭。
EN: His rebuttal is unfounded and full of baseless accusations.

ZH: 这样的指责纯属空口无凭。
EN: Such accusations are purely baseless.

ZH: 空口无凭的言论只会带来混乱。
EN: Baseless remarks will only bring chaos.

ZH: 不要轻易相信那些空口无凭的传闻。
EN: Don't easily believe those baseless rumors.

ZH: 他只是空口无凭地指责了她。
EN: He accused her without any evidence.

ZH: 空口无凭只会使局面更加混乱。
EN: Baseless accusations will only make the situation more chaotic.

ZH: 没有任何证据就要批评别人，这就是空口无凭。
EN: Criticizing others without any evidence is baseless.
